# 2g: unsigned powers
### `++pow`

Computes `a` raised to the power of `b`, producing an atom.

#### Accepts

`a` is an atom.

`b` is an atom.

#### Produces

An atom.

#### Source

    ++  pow                                                 
      ~/  %pow
      |=  [a=@ b=@]
      ?:  =(b 0)  1
      |-  ?:  =(b 1)  a
      =+  c=$(b (div b 2))
      =+  d=(mul c c)
      ?~  (dis b 1)  d  (mul d a)

#### Examples

    > (pow 2 6)
    64

    > (pow 6 2)
    36

    > (pow 7 (add 2 2))
    2.401

    > (pow 2 0)
    1

    > `@ux`(pow 0x1b 2)
    0x2d9



