### `++sqt`

Computes the square root of `a` and its remainder.

#### Accepts

`a` is an atom.

#### Produces

A cell of atoms.

#### Source
    ++  sqt                                               
      ~/  %sqt
      |=  a=@  ^-  [p=@ q=@]
      ?~  a  [0 0]
      =+  [q=(div (dec (xeb a)) 2) r=0]
      =-  [-.b (sub a +.b)]
      ^=  b  |-
      =+  s=(add r (bex q))
      =+  t=(mul s s)
      ?:  =(q 0)
        ?:((lte t a) [s t] [r (mul r r)])
      ?:  (lte t a)
        $(r s, q (dec q))
      $(q (dec q))

#### Examples

    > (sqt 4)
    [p=2 q=0]

    > (sqt 6)
    [p=2 q=2]

    > (sqt 2)
    [p=1 q=1]

    > (sqt 0b1101)
    [p=3 q=4]

    > `@ux`(sqt 0b1101)
    ! exit



